<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9DFFAEF4ACF88FFDDECC0F" bold="true" box="[199,552,1793,1820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Comparison with related taxa</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9DFFAEF65EF88CFD5BCC0F" box="[565,685,1794,1820]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Allozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9DFFAEF65EF88CFD5BCC0F" box="[565,685,1794,1820]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Allozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from all other genera by the presence of a well sclerotized, rounded, axial extension on the palp trochanter of the males (vs. extension absent (
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9DFFAEF0B0F8A8FF3DCC76" authority="Fain" authorityName="Fain" authorityYear="1989" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Afroheterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9DFFAEF0B0F8A8FA6ACC53" box="[1243,1436,1830,1856]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Afroheterozercon</emphasis>
Fain
</taxonomicName>
) or membranous (
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9DFFAEF5CAF8C4FDA0CC77" authorityName="Fain" authorityYear="1989" box="[417,598,1866,1892]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Amheterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9DFFAEF5CAF8C4FDA0CC77" box="[417,598,1866,1892]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Amheterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9DFFAEF603F8C5FCA9CC77" authority="Berlese" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[616,863,1866,1892]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Heterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9DFFAEF603F8C5FD08CC77" box="[616,766,1867,1892]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Heterozercon</emphasis>
Berlese
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9DFFAEF706F8C5FBB8CC77" authority="Fain" authorityName="Fain" authorityYear="1989" box="[877,1102,1866,1892]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Maracazercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9DFFAEF706F8C5FBF9CC77" box="[877,1039,1867,1892]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Maracazercon</emphasis>
Fain
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9DFFAEF037F8C4FACBCC77" authorityName="Gerdeman &amp; Klompen" authorityYear="2003" box="[1116,1341,1866,1892]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Narceoheterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9DFFAEF037F8C4FACBCC77" box="[1116,1341,1866,1892]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Narceoheterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9DFFAEF125F8C4FEE4CC9B" authority="Gerdeman &amp; Garcia &amp; Herczak &amp; Klompen, 2018" authorityName="Gerdeman &amp; Garcia &amp; Herczak &amp; Klompen" authorityYear="2018" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Philippinozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9DFFAEF125F8C4FEE4CC9B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Philippinozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C062BFF9DFFAEF570F8E0FE71CC9B" box="[283,391,1902,1928]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). The diagnostic character that the tarsus and tibia of legs I are distinctly narrower than the remaining segments of this leg, listed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A1AB3FF9DFFAEF60FF81CFD1CCCBF" author="Fain, A." box="[612,746,1938,1964]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="145 - 156" refId="ref8941" refString="Fain, A. (1989) Notes on mites associated with Myriapoda. IV. New taxa in the Heterozerconidae (Acari, Mesostigmata). Bulletin de l'Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 59, 145 - 156." type="journal article" year="1989">Fain (1989)</bibRefCitation>
, is rejected. The difference in relative thickness in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9DFFAEF14FF81CFA6ACCBF" box="[1316,1436,1938,1964]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Allozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9DFFAEF14FF81CFA6ACCBF" box="[1316,1436,1938,1964]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Allozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species vs. other heterozerconid genera is not always distinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9DFFAFF4ACF854FE9BCA0C" blockId="2.[151,1437,1361,2036]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,153,431]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9DFFAEF4ACF854FEE8CCE7" bold="true" box="[199,286,2010,2036]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Note 1:</emphasis>
The diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9DFFAEF583F854FD5CCCE7" authorityName="Fain" authorityYear="1989" box="[488,682,2010,2036]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Asioheterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9DFFAEF583F854FD5CCCE7" box="[488,682,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Asioheterozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not provide any distinguishing characters between that genus and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF4ADFF17FEC8CBA0" box="[198,318,153,179]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Allozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF4ADFF17FEC8CBA0" box="[198,318,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Allozercon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This is consistent with observations on specimens in the OSAL collection which represent multiple species, but which are all very similar. To avoid retaining two generic concepts that appear to cover the same group of mites and that cannot be distinguished, we propose 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF693FF6FFC05CBE8" authority="Fain" authorityName="Fain" authorityYear="1989" box="[760,1011,225,251]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Asioheterozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF693FF6FFC4CCBE8" box="[760,954,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Asioheterozercon</emphasis>
Fain
</taxonomicName>
as a subjective junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF111FF6FFE9BCA0C" authority="Vitzthum." authorityName="Vitzthum." class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Allozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF111FF6FFF00CA0C" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Allozercon</emphasis>
Vitzthum.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB46742FF9CFFAFF4ACFEA7FD09CABC" blockId="3.[151,1437,153,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF4ACFEA7FEEECA50" bold="true" box="[199,280,297,323]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Note 2</emphasis>
: The continued recognition of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF6EEFEA7FC99CA50" authority="Vitzthum" authorityName="Vitzthum" box="[645,879,297,323]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" genus="Allozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF6EEFEA7FD0BCA50" box="[645,765,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Allozercon</emphasis>
Vitzthum
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF7EAFEA7FBBCCA57" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1892" box="[897,1098,297,324]" class="Arachnida" family="Heterozerconidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Heterozerconidae</taxonomicName>
) could raise a nomenclatural problem as the same name was subsequently proposed for a genus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF7DBFEC3FB1DCA74" authority="(Blaszak, 1984)" authorityName="Blaszak" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Blaszak" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[944,1259,333,359]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Zerconidae (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A1AB3FF9CFFAFF056FEC3FB15CA74" author="Blaszak, C." box="[1085,1251,333,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" pagination="587 - 601" refId="ref8679" refString="Blaszak, C. (1984) Three new genera of zerconid mites (Acari, Mesostigmata, Zerconidae) from the United States of America with a key to the American genera. Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne, 53, 587 - 601." type="journal article" year="1984">Błaszak, 1984</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This issue was addressed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A1AB3FF9CFFAFF545FEFFFD06CA98" author="Kocak, A. O. &amp; Kemal, M." box="[302,752,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref9177" refString="Kocak, A. O. &amp; Kemal, M. (2008) Nomenclatural notes on the genus group names of the order Acarina. Miscellaneous Papers of the Centre for Entomological Studies Ankara, 145, 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2008">Koçak &amp; Kemal (Koçak &amp; Kemal, 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A1AB3FF9CFFAFF690FEFFFC0ECA98" author="Kemal, M. &amp; Kocak, A. O." box="[763,1016,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" pagination="147 - 148" refId="ref9127" refString="Kemal, M. &amp; Kocak, A. O. (2009) A replacement name for Blaszakia Kocak &amp; Kemal, 2008 in the family Zerconidae (Acarina, Mesostigmata). Miscellaneous Papers of the Centre for Entomological Studies Ankara, 147 - 148, 10." type="book chapter" year="2009">Kemal &amp; Koçak, 2009</bibRefCitation>
) who proposed the replacement name 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B1CC1FF9CFFAFF4FCFE1BFE00CABC" authority="Kemal &amp; Kocak" authorityName="Kemal &amp; Kocak" box="[151,502,405,431]" class="Arachnida" family="Zerconidae" genus="Blaszakzercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FBB50FF9CFFAFF4FCFE1BFECECABC" box="[151,312,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Blaszakzercon</emphasis>
Kemal &amp; Koçak
</taxonomicName>
for the zerconid genus.
</paragraph>
